==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Espalier
<hw>Es*pal"ier</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>espalier</ets>, fr. It. <ets>spalliera</ets>, fr. <ets>spalla</ets>
shoulder, the same word as F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧paule</ets>. See
<er>Epaulet</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>A railing or trellis
upon which fruit trees or shrubs are trained, as upon a wall; a tree or
row of trees so trained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And figs from standard and <qex>espalier</qex> join.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Espalier</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Espalier
<hw>Es*pal"ier</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Espaliered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Espaliering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To form an espalier of, or to
protect by an espalier.</def>⟦br⟧
